# Why Modules?

* Reusable code
* Avoid duplication
* Easy maintenance
* Production best practice

```
modules/
   ├── vpc/
   ├── iam/
   └── eks/
```

---

# VPC Module

### Creates

* VPC
* Internet Gateway
* Public Subnets
* Private Subnets
* Database Subnets
* Elastic IP
* NAT Gateway
* Route Tables
* Route Table Associations

### Why?

| Resource          | Purpose                      |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- |
| VPC               | Private AWS Network          |
| Public Subnet     | ALB, NAT Gateway             |
| Private Subnet    | EKS Worker Nodes             |
| Database Subnet   | RDS/Aurora                   |
| IGW               | Internet Access              |
| NAT Gateway       | Internet for Private Subnets |
| Route Table       | Traffic Rules                |
| Route Association | Attach Routes to Subnets     |

---

# Kubernetes Subnet Tags

Public

```text
kubernetes.io/role/elb = 1
```

Private

```text
kubernetes.io/role/internal-elb = 1
```

Used by AWS Load Balancer Controller.

---

# IAM Module

Creates

* EKS Cluster Role
* Worker Node Role
* Instance Profile
* IAM Policy Attachments

### Cluster Role

Trusted By

```
eks.amazonaws.com
```

Purpose

* Manage Kubernetes Control Plane

---

### Worker Node Role

Trusted By

```
ec2.amazonaws.com
```

Purpose

* Join Cluster
* Pull Images from ECR
* Configure CNI
* Talk to API Server

---

### Attached Policies

```
AmazonEKSClusterPolicy
AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy
AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy
AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryReadOnly
```

---

# EKS Module

Creates

* EKS Cluster
* Managed Node Group

### Control Plane

AWS Managed

* API Server
* Scheduler
* Controller Manager
* etcd

---

### Worker Nodes

* EC2 Instances
* Run Pods
* Join Cluster

